## рҹҡҖ Quick Start (Local)

### Prerequisites
- **Node.js** вүҘ 18 (recommended: 20 LTS)
- **PostgreSQL** вүҘ 15 (or Docker Desktop)
- **Redis** вүҘ 7 (or Docker Desktop)
- **npm** вүҘ 9

### 1. Clone & Install
```bash
git clone <your-repo-url> healthcare-erp
cd healthcare-erp
npm install
```

### 2. Configure Environment
```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your database credentials
```

### 3. Start Dependencies (Docker)
```bash
docker compose up -d postgres redis minio
```

### 4. Run Migrations
```bash
npm run migrate
```

### 5. Start Development
```bash
npm run dev
```
- Frontend: http://localhost:5173
- Backend: http://localhost:3000

---

## рҹ—„ Database Migrations

The project uses **Knex.js** for database management. All 14 migrations are in `packages/backend/migrations/`.

```bash
# Run all pending migrations
npm run migrate

# Make a new migration
cd packages/backend
npx knex migrate:make my_migration --knexfile knexfile.ts

# Rollback last batch
npx knex migrate:rollback --knexfile knexfile.ts

# Check status
npx knex migrate:status --knexfile knexfile.ts
```

### Migration Files

| # | File | Tables Created |
|---|---|---|
| 001 | `initial_schema` | tenants, users, roles, patients, appointments, emr_records, invoices, branches, payment_transactions |
| 002 | `clinical_modules` | lab_catalog, lab_orders, lab_tests, pharmacy_prescriptions, pharmacy_inventory, radiology_orders, referrals, nursing_notes, nursing_tasks, telemedicine_sessions, home_visits, queue_entries, notifications |
| 003 | `operations` | employees, attendance, leave_requests, payroll_runs, inventory_items, inventory_transactions, insurance_companies, insurance_claims, documents, document_versions, form_definitions, form_submissions, compliance_policies, compliance_audits, crm_campaigns, breach_log, data_consent_logs |
| 004 | `intelligence` | dashboard_definitions, dashboard_widgets, kpi_definitions, ai_hub_models, ai_model_predictions |
| 005 | `scale` | tenant_subscriptions, tenant_domains, usage_records, tenant_data_residency |
| 006 | `patient_experience` | booking_slots, booking_requests, patient_messages, patient_shared_documents, appointment_reminders, telemedicine_waiting_room, telemedicine_chat_messages |
| 007 | `platform_maturity` | api_keys, api_key_logs, system_alerts, system_metrics, export_definitions, export_jobs, cache_configs |
| 008 | `experience` | import_jobs, user_settings, notification_preferences |
| 009 | `communications` | user_sessions, print_templates, communications_log |
| 010 | `intelligence` | dw_patient_stats, dw_appointment_stats, dw_revenue_stats, automation_rules, automation_logs, barcode_registry |
| 011 | `automation_digital` | automation_rules (v2), automation_rule_actions, automation_execution_logs, barcode_templates, barcode_labels, barcode_scan_logs |
| 012 | `security_communication` | password_resets, otp_codes, audit_logs, notification_templates, notification_logs |
| 013 | _(not used)_ | вҖ” |
| 014 | `clinical_reference` | patient_allergies, medication_database, icd10_codes |

